# Dysphor UI Guidelines

The UI implementation should follow the design shown in the [index.html](mdc:index.html) prototype. This document outlines key UI elements and style guidelines.

## Color Scheme

- **Primary Color**: #7F5AF0 (purple)
- **Dark Background**: #16161A (dark neutral)
- **Card Background**: #24263A (dark card)
- **Light Text**: #E0E0E0
- **Subtle Text**: #94A3B8
- **Accent Green**: #2CB67D (for work timer)
- **Accent Red**: #FF6B6B (for break timer)

## Screen Structure

### Pomodoro Timer Screen
- Circular progress indicator showing remaining time
- Timer display in center (MM:SS format)
- Status text below timer
- Control buttons (reset, play/pause, skip)
- Stats cards showing completed cycles and total focus time

### Milestones Screen
- List of milestone cards with:
  - Emoji icon
  - Title and description
  - Days remaining count
- Add button at bottom

### History Screen
- List of completed pomodoro sessions
- Each item shows title, completion time, and duration
- Edit capability for session titles
- Clear all button in header

### Settings Screen
- Input fields for timer durations
- Toggle switches for notification options
- Stats display (streak count)

## Navigation

Bottom navigation bar with four tabs:
1. Focus (clock icon)
2. Milestones (calendar icon)
3. History (history icon)
4. Settings (gear icon)

## Widget Styling

- Use rounded corners (borderRadius: 20) for cards
- Apply shadows to elevate cards
- Use consistent padding (16-20px)
- Follow the color scheme strictly
- Implement proper status indicators and feedback

## Implementation Notes

- Don't use custom fonts (system fonts only)
- Don't use local images or cached_network_image
- Simplify notifications (button only, no actual functionality)
- Use setState for state management
- Use shared_preferences for data persistence
